            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .bylaws-section p {
            margin: 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Subdivision Bylaws</h1>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article I: Name and Purpose</h2>
        <p><strong>Name:</strong> The name of the subdivision shall be [Subdivision Name].</p>
        <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of these bylaws is to establish rules and regulations governing the use, maintenance, and management of the subdivision to promote the health, safety, and general welfare of the community.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article II: Definitions</h2>
        <p><strong>Association:</strong> Refers to the [Subdivision Name] Homeowners Association (HOA).</p>
        <p><strong>Board:</strong> Refers to the Board of Directors of the Association.</p>
        <p><strong>Common Areas:</strong> Includes all areas of the subdivision that are not privately owned and maintained, including parks, playgrounds, and other communal facilities.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article III: Membership</h2>
        <p><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Membership in the Association is mandatory for all property owners within the subdivision.</p>
        <p><strong>Dues:</strong> Each member is required to pay annual dues as set by the Board to cover the costs of maintenance and management of the common areas.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article IV: Meetings</h2>
        <p><strong>Annual Meetings:</strong> The Association shall hold an annual meeting to discuss and vote on matters affecting the subdivision.</p>
        <p><strong>Special Meetings:</strong> Special meetings may be called by the Board or by a petition of at least 20% of the members.</p>
        <p><strong>Quorum:</strong> A quorum for any meeting shall be defined as at least 30% of the members.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article V: Board of Directors</h2>
        <p><strong>Composition:</strong> The Board shall consist of [number] members elected by the Association members.</p>
        <p><strong>Duties:</strong> The Board is responsible for managing the affairs of the Association, including enforcing bylaws and managing the common areas.</p>
        <p><strong>Terms:</strong> Board members shall serve terms of [number] years and may be re-elected.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article VI: Rules and Regulations</h2>
        <p><strong>General Use:</strong> All members must comply with the rules and regulations set forth by the Association, including those pertaining to noise, property maintenance, and use of common areas.</p>
        <p><strong>Architectural Review:</strong> Any modifications to the exterior of properties must be approved by the Architectural Review Committee.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article VII: Assessments</h2>
        <p><strong>Regular Assessments:</strong> The Board shall determine and levy regular assessments for the maintenance of common areas and other expenses.</p>
        <p><strong>Special Assessments:</strong> Special assessments may be levied for extraordinary expenses, subject to a majority vote of the members.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article VIII: Enforcement</h2>
        <p><strong>Violation:</strong> Any member found to be in violation of these bylaws may be subject to fines or other penalties as determined by the Board.</p>
        <p><strong>Appeal:</strong> Members have the right to appeal any penalties or fines to the Board.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article IX: Amendments</h2>
        <p><strong>Proposal:</strong> Amendments to these bylaws may be proposed by the Board or by a petition of at least 20% of the members.</p>
        <p><strong>Approval:</strong> Amendments must be approved by a two-thirds majority of members present at a duly called meeting.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bylaws-section">
        <h2>Article X: Miscellaneous</h2>
        <p><strong>Severability:</strong> If any provision of these bylaws is found to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.</p>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> In case of any conflict between these bylaws and applicable local or state laws, the latter shall prevail.</p>
    </div>
</body>
